    "methodology": "Admissions data covers finished admission episodes (FAEs) in NHS hospitals in England where the primary or secondary diagnosis was coded as intentional self-harm (ICD-10 X60-X84). Rates per 100,000 are age-standardised using the European Standard Population 2013. The 2020 dip reflects reduced A&E attendance during COVID-19 lockdowns, not a genuine decline in self-harm.",
    "knownIssues": [
      "ICD-10 coding practices vary between trusts — some under-record self-harm as primary diagnosis",
      "COVID-19 lockdowns in 2020 caused a temporary drop in admissions that does not reflect true prevalence",
      "Hospital admissions capture only the most severe presentations — estimated to represent 10-15% of all self-harm episodes"
    ]
